column1: #Text=Wikinews interviews Spanish Paralympic track and field athlete Elena Congost Mohedano
#Text=Laura Hale interviews Elena Congost Mohedano for Wikinews
#Text=Elena Congost Mohedano at the airport in Madrid before departing for France

#Text=With the IPC Athletics World Championships scheduled to start this Friday , Wikinews interviewed Spanish T12 classified long distance runner Elena Congost Mohedano at Madrid – Barajas Airport Monday before he departed for Lyon , France .
#Text=Congost is scheduled to compete in the T12 1500 meters .
#Text=Hello , I 'm interviewing Elena Congost Mohedano who is a Spanish Paralympic athlete who won a silver in London and is going to Lyon to compete in the 2013 IPC Athletics World Championships .
#Text=Having won a medal in London are you going to get another one in this one ?
#Text=I train all year to go to win a medal .
#Text=And you do n't train/run with a guide because you 're , what , T-13 ?
#Text=So you have a degenerative eye disease , so your vision is getting worse ?
#Text=Do you expect it to get much worse over your continued history competing ?
#Text=Now it 's stalled , but next year it 's possible .
#Text=Do you plan to stick since you 've been competing since 2002 , right ... ?
#Text=Do you plan to continue running until 2020 if Madrid gets the Games ?
#Text=There 's so few women competing for Spain .
#Text=Is that an additional challenge as an athlete in this country ?
#Text=In this country there are more girls in 100m , 200m and long jump .
#Text=Why do you think there 's so few women on the Spanish team ?
#Text=It 's like 27 total Spanish competing , and there 's like [ three ] women ?
#Text=The level is high internationally , but in Spain ... no more level .
#Text=Someone with a visual impairement , there 's a lot of sports you could do ?
#Text=With so many sporting opportunities for people with vision impairments
#Text=in Spain , why did you choose track and field ?
#Text=When I was young , my dream was to become an athlete .
#Text=I saw them in tv , in races , and I told my parents " my wish is to win a gold medal in the Olympics ! "
#Text=Is there any particular athlete you remember from when you were young being particularly inspiring ?
#Text=Do people ever comment to you about them ?
#Text=Because in the US they were like , " your uniforms look like McDonald 's ! "
#Text=Spanish language : ‍¿Hay alguien que ha dicho algo de lo que es el color y tal , porque por lo visto en EE .
#Text=In London , everyone said they were not good ... They said we looked like clowns .
#Text=As somebody who 's been competing for more than ten years , has there been a big change in the Paralympic movement from your perspective ?
#Text=In the Paralympics , every four years I increase my performance level .
#Text=Do you think that the increased competition has made you a better athlete ?
